overview: The user initiated a request to implement a database and an admin
  dashboard for a sleep questionnaire application, referencing a Statement of
  Work. The primary goal was to store questionnaire responses, enable CSV data
  export, and provide a secure client login for data access. After an initial
  codebase evaluation, it was determined that a database schema for responses,
  API routes for data handling, an authentication system, and an admin dashboard
  were missing. Key decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for
  the database, implementing a simple password-based authentication via
  environment variables and HTTP-only cookies, and combining demographic data
  fields to include year of birth, sex, zip code, weight, and height. The
  implementation began with successfully updating the demographic types,
